ope|first4=James E|last5=Marletto|first5=Chiara|last6=Kay|first6=Alastair|last7=Scarani|first7=Valerio|last8=Ekert|first8=Artur|bibcode=2012PhRvL.109p0404K|arxiv=1202.3571}}</ref>\n*New low overhead method for fault-tolerant quantum logic developed, called lattice surgery<ref>\nDecember 7, 2012\n{{Cite journal\n | title=Surface code quantum computing by lattice surgery\n | doi=10.1088/1367-2630/14/12/123011\n | volume=14\n | issue=12\n | journal=New J. Phys.\n | page=123011|arxiv=1111.4022\n | year=2012\n | last1=Horsman\n | first1=C\n | last2=Fowler\n | first2=A. G\n | last3=Devitt\n | first3=S. J\n | last4=Van Meter\n | first4=R\n | bibcode=2012NJPh...14l3011H\n }}</ref>\n\n===2013===\n* Coherence time of 39 minutes at room temperature (and 3 hours at cryogenic temperatures) demonstrated for an ensemble of impurity-spin qubits in isotopically purified silicon.<ref name=\"39 minutes\">{{cite web | url=https://www.theverge.com/2013/11/14/5104668/qubits-stored-for-39-minutes-quantum-computer-new-record | title=Researchers smash through quantum computer storage record | publisher=The Verge | website=Webzine | date=November 14, 2013 | accessdate=November 20, 2013 | author=Kastrenakes, Jacob}}</ref>\n* Extension of time for qubit maintained in superimposed state for ten times longer than what has ever been achieved before<ref>{{cite web | url=http://welldonestuff.com/quantum-computer-breakthrough-2013/ | title=Quantum Computer Breakthrough 2013| date=November 24, 2013}}</ref>\n*First resource analysis of a large-scale quantum algorithm using explicit fault-tolerant, error-correction protocols was developed for factoring<ref>\nOctober 10, 2013\n{{Cite journal\n | title=Requirements for fault-tolerant factoring on an atom-optics quantum computer\n | doi=10.1038/ncomms3524\n | pmid=24088785\n | volume=4\n | journal=Nature Communications\n | page=2524|arxiv=1212.4934\n | year=2013\n | last1=Devitt\n | first1=S. J\n | last2=Stephens\n | first2=A. M\n | last3=Munro\n | first3