 Right\n | url=https://www.wired.com/wiredscience/2010/01/quantum-computer-hydrogen-simulation/\n | accessdate=February 5, 2010\n | work=Wired\n | date=January 28, 2010}}</ref>\n* First germanium laser brings us closer to optical computers<ref>\nFebruary 4, 2010\n{{Cite news\n |author=Larry Hardesty \n |title=First germanium laser brings us closer to 'optical computers' \n |url=http://www.physorg.com/news184493799.html \n |accessdate=February 4, 2010 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111224181702/http://www.physorg.com/news184493799.html \n |archivedate=December 24, 2011 \n |df=mdy \n}}</ref>\n* Single electron qubit developed<ref>\nFebruary 6, 2010\n{{Cite news\n | author=Science Daily\n | title=Quantum Computing Leap Forward: Altering a Lone Electron Without Disturbing Its Neighbors\n | url=https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2010/02/100205162953.htm\n | accessdate=February 6, 2010}}</ref>\n* Quantum state in macroscopic object<ref>\nMarch 18, 2010\n{{Cite news\n | author=Jason Palmer\n | title=Team's quantum object is biggest by factor of billions\n | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/sci/tech/8570836.stm\n | accessdate=March 20, 2010\n|work=BBC News\n| date=March 17, 2010}}</ref>\n* New quantum computer cooling method developed<ref>{{Cite news|author=University of Cambridge |title=Cambridge discovery could pave the way for quantum computing |url=http://www.articleant.com/p/re/65605-cambridge-discovery-could-pave-the-way-for-quantum-computing.html |accessdate=March 20, 2010 }}{{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>\n*Racetrack ion trap developed<ref>\nApril 1, 2010\n{{Cite news\n | author=ScienceDaily\n | title=Racetrack Ion Trap Is a Contender in Quantum Computing Quest\n | url=https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2010/04/100401130336.htm\n | accessdate=April 3, 2010}}</ref>\n*Evidence for a Moore-Read state in the <math>\nu=5/2</math> quantum Hall plateau,<ref>April 21, 2010\n{{Cite news\n | author=Rice 