.harvard.edu/urn-3:HUL.InstRepos:12132060\n | type=Submitted manuscript\n }}\n</ref><ref>\n{{cite news\n| url=http://techland.time.com/2012/07/06/quantum-computing-at-room-temperature-now-a-reality/\n| title=Quantum Computing at Room Temperature - Now a Reality\n| work=Magazine/Periodical\n| date=July 6, 2012\n| agency=Time Magazine (Techland) Time Inc.\n| accessdate=August 5, 2012\n| author=Peckham, Matt\n| pages=1}}</ref>\n*Theory of Bell-based randomness expansion with reduced assumption of measurement independence.<ref>{{Cite journal |doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.109.160404|pmid=23350071|title=Effects of Reduced Measurement Independence on Bell-Based Randomness Expansion|journal=Physical Review Letters|volume=109|issue=16|pages=160404|year=2012|last1=Koh|first1=Dax Enshan|last2=Hall|first2=Michael J. W|last3=Setiawan|last4=Pope|first4=James E|last5=Marletto|first5=Chiara|last6=Kay|first6=Alastair|last7=Scarani|first7=Valerio|last8=Ekert|first8=Artur|bibcode=2012PhRvL.109p0404K|arxiv=1202.3571}}</ref>\n*New low overhead method for fault-tolerant quantum logic developed, called lattice surgery<ref>\nDecember 7, 2012\n{{Cite journal\n | title=Surface code quantum computing by lattice surgery\n | doi=10.1088/1367-2630/14/12/123011\n | volume=14\n | issue=12\n | journal=New J. Phys.\n | page=123011|arxiv=1111.4022\n | year=2012\n | last1=Horsman\n | first1=C\n | last2=Fowler\n | first2=A. G\n | last3=Devitt\n | first3=S. J\n | last4=Van Meter\n | first4=R\n | bibcode=2012NJPh...14l3011H\n }}</ref>\n\n===2013===\n* Coherence time of 39 minutes at room temperature (and 3 hours at cryogenic temperatures) demonstrated for an ensemble of impurity-spin qubits in isotopically purified silicon.<ref name=\"39 minutes\">{{cite web | url=https://www.theverge.com/2013/11/14/5104668/qubits-stored-for-39-minutes-quantum-computer-new-record | title=Researchers smash through quantum computer storage record | publisher=The Verge | website=Webzine | date=14 November 2013 | accessdate=20 No